column5: I thought they stopped making Extra Stock, at least that's what the beer store told us two years ago. My buddies had to listen to me whine all trip because that was my favorite.

Per high recommendations, I'm going to give Crystal a try this year. Bought Blue at the border last year, but need to get the high test Canadian stuff this time. Where is a good place near a grocery store in Dryden to get booze?
Compared to U.S. beers, blue is high test, besides it is the beer everyone will like.
I understand that's if you buy it in Canada, I bought it in International Falls so I believe it had a lower alcohol content.
Kokanee,Moosehead.FISH ON!
Got to watch that high test stuff.....if you are not carefull it comes with a price.......paid in the morning.
free stuff is the best!
PilznerOld SaskatchewanCanadianBohOr ... whatever YOU got.
Kokanee and Labbats Maxima Ice
LABATTS BLUE ICE COLD. 12(OZ.)
Alright everyone, when you go to Canada what brand of beer is your favorite? This is Canadian brands and not US brands. Oh leaving for Reindeer Lake tomorrow morning :)
LABATTS EXTRA STOCK. SO STRONG IT ONLY COMES IN A SIX PACK

I personally drink Coors Light but if you are coming to Saskatchewan you have to drink Pilsner or Canadian. Try some Calgary too if you can find it. It must be all right as my uncle seems to drink them fairly steadily.Have fun at Reindeer!!!
Blue!
Kokenee or Moosehead
I like Crystal and OV
Labatts Light is very popular.
Try 'em all and when you return, you can advise the rest of us.
Keith's Pale Ale, Northern Brewers Superior, Blue, and anything else as long as it's in a bottle.
The Best Canadian Beer...Any beer you drink with Canadian walleyes and two of your fishing buddies.That's the best!!!
